<item>
            <title>[SPARK-13519] Driver should tell Executor to stop itself when cleaning executor&apos;s state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-13519</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the driver removes an executor&apos;s state, the connection between the driver and the executor may be still alive so that the executor cannot exit automatically (E.g., Master will send RemoveExecutor when a work is lost but the executor is still alive), so the driver try to tell the executor to stop itself. Otherwise, we will leak an executor.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
